  "text": "Through the use of an established rat model of nutrient restriction during pregnancy [CITATION_1] , the following study sets out to determine how early life nutritionally induced fetal growth restriction impacts neonatal, prepubertal, and young adult ovarian signaling pathways involved in primordial follicle recruitment, follicle growth, and steroidogenic regulators mediate ovarian follicle loss.",
